The paper deals with the application of AI systems to complex tasks that involve interaction with humans, specifically in the context of reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the AI and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the role of human intervention in preventing catastrophic mistakes during training, which suggests that it may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of supervised learning to imitate human intervention decisions, which suggests that it may belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed approach, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
